description: Core Wazir engineering rules — roles, workflows, TDD, verification
alwaysApply: true
---

wazir-core:

- Wazir is a host-native engineering OS kit for Claude, Codex, Gemini, and Cursor.
- `roles/` defines canonical role contracts. Each role has defined inputs, outputs, escalation rules, and failure conditions.
- `workflows/` defines phase entrypoints. Every task flows through 14 phases with 9 hard approval gates.
- Default live run state lives outside the repo under `~/.wazir/projects/<project-slug>/`.
- Generated host exports come from canonical sources. Run `wazir export build` to regenerate.
- TDD, conventional commits, and verification-before-completion are mandatory.
- Use isolated feature branches.

key-references:

- `wazir.manifest.yaml` — project manifest and schema
- `docs/concepts/architecture.md` — system architecture
- `docs/concepts/roles-and-workflows.md` — role and phase concepts
- `docs/reference/roles-reference.md` — role and workflow lookup tables
